TECH_PARAM_1.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Flag indicating the status of the Float (see manual) (could be reported as hex)

TECH_PARAM_2.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Pressure measured once for each test message block [centibars]
TECH_PARAM_2.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: test message data reporting pressure at the surface during drift - cycle 0

TECH_PARAM_4.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Air bladder pressure measured once for each test message block [counts]

TECH_PARAM_5.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Quiescent battery voltage measured once for each test message block [counts]
TECH_PARAM_5.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: battery voltage during inactive surface phase

TECH_PARAM_6.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of TSP samples in this message block
TECH_PARAM_6.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: total number of slices of the ascending profile after reduction

TECH_PARAM_7.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Same as the Test Message 1 Status word
TECH_PARAM_7.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Flag indicating the status of the Float (see manual) (could be reported as hex)

TECH_PARAM_8.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Surface pressure at end of Up Time [centibars]
TECH_PARAM_8.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Surface pressure recorded just before the previous descent - Note: cumulative offset, This IS NOT used to correct pressure on board Not autocorrected

TECH_PARAM_9.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: The current pressure [centibars] As recorded during the creation of each argos message block. Each distinct copy of argos message #1 contains a new pressure measurement.
TECH_PARAM_9.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: test message data reporting pressure at the surface during drift - cycle 0

TECH_PARAM_10.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Piston position, recorded as the instrument reaches the surface

TECH_PARAM_11.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Piston position at end of Park phase [counts]
TECH_PARAM_11.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: piston position at end of park period before descent to profile depth

TECH_PARAM_12.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Piston position at end of last Deep descent phase [counts]
TECH_PARAM_12.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: piston position at maximum profile pressure

TECH_PARAM_13.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: This long-word records the state of 32 status bits specifically related to the SBE41. Individual bits can be accessed with an appropriate bit-mask. 16 bits
TECH_PARAM_13.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Flag indicating the status of the CTD (see manual) (could be reported as hex)

TECH_PARAM_14.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Battery voltage at end of Park phase [counts]
TECH_PARAM_14.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: battery voltage measured at end of park with no load

TECH_PARAM_15.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Battery current at end of Park phase [counts]
TECH_PARAM_15.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: battery current measured at end of park, before descent to profile depth

TECH_PARAM_16.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Battery voltage while SBE41 sampling at end of Park phase [counts]
TECH_PARAM_16.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: battery voltage measured when the SBE41 sampled after the end of park phase

TECH_PARAM_17.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Battery current while SBE41 sampling at end of Park phase [counts]
TECH_PARAM_17.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: battery current measured when the SBE41 sampled at the end of park

TECH_PARAM_18.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Battery voltage measured just before the end of the initial piston extension beginning Profile phase [counts]
TECH_PARAM_18.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: battery voltage jus before profile begins - no load on the batteries

TECH_PARAM_19.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Battery current measured just before the end of the initial piston extension beginning Profile phase [counts]
TECH_PARAM_19.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Battery Current measured at bottom (park or pressure) at initial pump extension completion

TECH_PARAM_20.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Battery voltage while air pump running [counts]
TECH_PARAM_20.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Voltage measured when AIR PUMP is switched on at the surface for extra buoyancy

TECH_PARAM_21.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Battery current while air pump running [counts]
TECH_PARAM_21.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Battery Current measured at the surface with the air pump running (6 seconds)

TECH_PARAM_22.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Air bladder pressure measured once for each test message block [counts]

TECH_PARAM_23.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: The number of 6-second pulses of the air pump required to inflate the air bladder
TECH_PARAM_23.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of 6-second pulses of the air pump required to inflate the air bladder

TECH_PARAM_24.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Integrated Measure of (Volt-Sec) of volume of air pumped during telemetry cycle.
TECH_PARAM_24.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: integrated measure (volts * seconds) of the pumped air volume (VSAP of Apex floats)

TECH_PARAM_25.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of active-ballast adjustments made during the park phase
TECH_PARAM_25.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of times the float readjusts its buoyancy during park phase - using either the pump or EV

TECH_PARAM_26.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of hourly park-level PT samples
TECH_PARAM_26.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of samples collected during park phase

TECH_PARAM_27.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Internal vacuum at end of Park phase [counts]
TECH_PARAM_27.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Internal Vacuum at end of park. before descent to profile depth

TECH_PARAM_28.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Cumulative piston on time during ascent [seconds]

TECH_PARAM_29.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: The ice evasion record for the most recent 8 profiles. The most recent profile is in the position of the least significant bit. Asserted bits indicate profiles where the ice-detection algorithm terminated true.
TECH_PARAM_29.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: aborted profile count - increments by one for each profile interrupted by ice detection. If units are 'bit' then represents the ice evasion record for the last 8 profiles with the latest profile in the least significant bit.

TECH_PARAM_30.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of CTD samples taken in the mixed layer

TECH_PARAM_31.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: The infimum of the mixed-layer median temperature since the last successful telemetry
TECH_PARAM_31.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: infimum of the mixed-layer median temperature since the last successful telemetry

TECH_PARAM_32.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: The maximum (in absolute value) divergence between pressures from closely-spaced (ie., a few seconds apart in time) P-only sample requests and PT or PTS sample requests. The divergence is measured as the P-only sample minus the pressure from the PTS (or PT) sample. The difference is measured in centibars.
TECH_PARAM_32.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: The maximum (in absolute value) divergence between pressures from closely-spaced (ie., a few seconds apart in time) P-only sample requests and PT or PTS sample requests. The divergence is measured as the P-only sample minus the pressure from the PTS (or PT) sample.

TECH_PARAM_33.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Profile initiation time (minutes) 2's compliment signed integer (positive values - profile initiated after down time expired, negative values - profile initiated before down time expired)

TECH_PARAM_34.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of pressure samples collected as the float descends from the Shallow to the park pressure.

TECH_PARAM_35.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: total number of Argos positions received.

TECH_PARAM_37.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: positioning (ARGOS message) - Class 1 - accuracy better than 1500m radius

TECH_PARAM_38.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: positioning (ARGOS message) - Class 2 - accuracy better than 500m radius

TECH_PARAM_39.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: positioning (ARGOS message) - Class 3 - accuracy better than 250m radius
